As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 491 people, 179 households, and 132 families residing in the village. The population density was {{convert|1,119.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 191 housing units at an average density of {{convert|435.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the village was 97.35% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.43% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.81% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.41% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.61% of the population.

There were 179 households, out of which 42.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 55.9% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 15.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 25.7% were non-families. 19.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 9.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.74 and the average family size was 3.20.

In the village, the population was spread out, with 30.8% under the age of 18, 5.7% from 18 to 24, 32.8% from 25 to 44, 20.0% from 45 to 64, and 10.8% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35 years. For every 100 females, there were 91.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.1 males.

The median income for a household in the village was $56,250, and the median income for a family was $59,583. Males had a median income of $34,808 versus $28,750 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the village was $20,989. About 7.2% of families and 4.4% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 7.4% of those under age 18 and none of those age 65 or over.

